"7:65:1" : {s: 7, a: 65, w: 1, r: "", t: "وَإِلَىٰ", l: "إِلَىٰ", lc: 742, tl: "wa-ilā", lb: "পর্যন্ত, দিকে",e: "And to", b: "কাছে", f: 10, rm: ""},
"7:65:2" : {s: 7, a: 65, w: 2, r: "عود", t: "عَادٍ", l: "عَاد2", lc: 24, tl: "ʿādin", lb: "আদ জাতি",e: "Aad", b: "সীমালংঘন করে", f: 9, rm: "to return, turn away, come back, repeat, restore. aidun - one who returns. maadun - place where one returns, another name of Makkah. aada (vb. 4) - to cause to return, restore. The verb aada is transitive to mean to get some one return or cause to return or bring back (what has passed away)."},
