"7:66:8" : {s: 7, a: 66, w: 8, r: "راي", t: "لَنَرَىٰكَ", l: "رَءَا", lc: 271, tl: "lanarāka", lb: "(ভেবে/চোখে/স্বপ্ন) দেখা, উপলব্ধি করা",e: "surely, see you", b: "তোমাকে দেখতে পাচ্ছি", f: 3, rm: "to see/think/hold, in opinion of, perceive, judge, consider, know. araitaka / araitakum - do tell me thou/you (the personal pronoun ك is added for emphasis and is not purely as pleonism without adding to the meaning). tarani is for a compound word of a verb tara followed by a pronoun ni - you see me. badi al-rayi - having superficial view, outward appearance, first thought, apparently, without proper consideration. rayalain - to see with naked eye, judgement by sight. riyun - outward appearance, make a show. ruya - vision dream. alam tara - behold! lo! riaun - hypocrisy, ostentation, to be seen. taraa - to see one another, consider, come in sight of one another. yurauna - they deceive hypocritically assuming a false appearance."},
"7:66:9" : {s: 7, a: 66, w: 9, r: "", t: "فِى", l: "فِى", lc: 1675, tl: "fee", lb: "ভেতরে, মধ্যে",e: "in", b: "মধ্যে", f: 1184, rm: ""},
"7:66:10" : {s: 7, a: 66, w: 10, r: "سفه", t: "سَفَاهَةٍۢ", l: "سَفَاهَة", lc: 2, tl: "safāhatin", lb: "বোকামী",e: "foolishness", b: "নির্বোধ", f: 1, rm: ""},
"7:66:11" : {s: 7, a: 66, w: 11, r: "", t: "وَإِنَّا", l: "إِنّ", lc: 1536, tl: "wainna", lb: "(জোর দিয়ে বলা) অবশ্যই, নিসন্দেহে",e: "and indeed, we", b: "এবং নিশ্চই আমরা", f: 33, rm: ""},
"7:66:12" : {s: 7, a: 66, w: 12, r: "ظنن", t: "لَنَظُنُّكَ", l: "ظَنَّ", lc: 47, tl: "lanaẓunnuka", lb: "মনে করা, ভাবা, ধারণা/ অনুমান করা",e: "[we] think you", b: "তোমাকে মনে করি", f: 1, rm: "To think, suppose, doubt, assume, deem, believe, know, imagine, suspect, conjunctive, be sure of something in view of ones observations. As a general rule often this verb is succeeded by anna or an, that means to be sure about."},
"7:66:13" : {s: 7, a: 66, w: 13, r: "", t: "مِنَ", l: "مِن", lc: 3067, tl: "mina", lb: "মধ্য থেকে, কিছুর চেয়ে",e: "(are) of", b: "থেকে", f: 412, rm: ""},
"7:66:14" : {s: 7, a: 66, w: 14, r: "كذب", t: "ٱلْكَٰذِبِينَ", l: "كَٰذِب", lc: 32, tl: "l-kādhibīna", lb: "মিথ্যাবাদী",e: "the liars", b: "মিথ্যাবাদীদের (উপর)", f: 10, rm: "To lie, say what is not a fact, lie to falsely invent, tell lies about or against, fabricate a lie, relate a lie, say a falsehood, be wrong, be cut off, deceive, disappoint the expectation of."},
"7:67:1" : {s: 7, a: 67, w: 1, r: "قول", t: "قَالَ", l: "قَالَ", lc: 1618, tl: "qāla", lb: "কথা বলা",e: "He said", b: "সে বলল", f: 412, rm: "to say/speak, to call, to be named, word/speech, utterance, a thing said, greeting, discourse, one who says/speaks. To inspire/transmit/relate/answer/think/profess, emit an opinion on, indicate a state or condition or circumstance. qailun - speaker, indicator."},
"7:67:2" : {s: 7, a: 67, w: 2, r: "قوم", t: "يَٰقَوْمِ", l: "قَوْم", lc: 383, tl: "yāqawmi", lb: "লোকেরা, জনগোষ্ঠী",e: "O my people", b: "হে আমার জাতি", f: 38, rm: "stand still or firm, rose/stand up, managed/conducted/ordered/regulated/superintended, established, made it straight/right, maintain/erect/observe/perform, set up, people/community/company, abode, stature/dignity/rank. aqama - to keep a thing or an affair in a right state."},
